<subSubSection id="C31428808560145AE796FAB3FBED02F6" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB17B0B8560145AE796FAB3FBED02F6" blockId="10.[151,1437,715,1425]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis id="B97AA7198560145AE796FAB3FEEA022E" bold="true" box="[199,308,1328,1352]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">Remarks</emphasis>
. Resurrected genus and formerly a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E00888560145AE4E0FAB2FB0B022E" authority="Kottelat, 2013" authorityName="Kottelat" authorityYear="2013" box="[945,1237,1327,1352]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97AA7198560145AE4E0FAB2FBCD022E" box="[945,1043,1329,1352]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">Dasyatis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF9F06FA8560145AE375FAACFB13022E" author="Kottelat" box="[1060,1229,1327,1352]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" refString="Kottelat, M. (2013) The fishes of the inland waters of southeast Asia: a catalogue and core bibliography of the fishes known to occur in freshwaters, mangroves and estuaries. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 27, 1 - 663." type="journal article" year="2013">Kottelat, 2013</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, it consists of 10 morphologically similar species formerly placed in 
<emphasis id="B97AA7198560145AE589FAD6FC9C020A" box="[728,834,1365,1388]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">
<taxonomicName id="4C0E00888560145AE589FAD6FCE0020A" box="[728,830,1365,1388]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Dasyatis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The group is under review (PL); some of the nominal species listed above may be synonyms but other un-named species appear to exist.
</paragraph>
